28:
That was a bit overkill, don't you
think?
32:
Sorry about that! Mia and I ended
up going way far off, it took us a bit
of time to get back!
38:
Ahh! Help me!
How are you supposed to STOP this
thing?!
43:
So, those creatures were after this
boy here?
46:
Oh dear, isn't he just a cutie!
Where'd you find him?
51:
Wait... Is that the same crystal as
mine?
But that belonged to Captain
Zegra... How...
69:
Don't you worry—you're in good
company here!
73:
Just relax. Nobody here's gonna eat
you. What's your name, kid?
76:
Huh? What's with that spooked
reaction? You're beastfolk too, aren't
you?
80:
As far as beastfolk go, we might be
on a slightly different... level than
he's used to.
83:
Tsk, whatever. If he's got ears and a
tail, he's one of us as far as I'm
concerned!
92:
My name... is Luca.
Thank you for helping me.
101:
And I'm Nimbus.
The loudmouthed thief over here is
Mia.
107: I prefer the term treasure hunter!
111:
We've got grub if you're hungry,
Luca. Come with us.
115:
It's all right, you can go! They're
wonderful people, I'm sure you'll get
along.
119:
I see, so your name's Luca, huh? At
any rate, it's a good thing you got
out of that in one piece. We were all
pretty worried for you!
124: I... I'm very grateful for your help.
129:
Are you okay, Luca? Your face is
totally red! Maybe you're still not
feeling well after all? Hehe.
133:
All right, let's leave the poor kid
alone. We'll never get anywhere if
we spend all night picking on him.
137:
First, allow me to introduce myself.
The name is Marina. Are you familiar
with the Crimson Blades?
141:
The Crimson Blades? Does that
mean you... worked for my father?
144:
I suspected as much. You're Captain
Zegra's kid, huh?
147:
That crystal of yours—I happen to
have one just like it.
150:
Father left you a piece of the
Genome Quartz as well?
153:
I don't know about "leaving" it to
me... I guess it just came into my
possession.
157:
Fascinating! This must be the
inheritance of Captain Zegra!
160:
The Captain disappeared five years
ago. It was even rumored that many
in the Crimson Blades worked under
him!
164:
Working under him, huh? I can't
blame people for thinking that. He
did take me under his wing.
168:
Luca, let's try something. Why don't
we touch our crystals together?
177:
Incredible! Now this is treasure to
get excited about! But wait...
180:
Something doesn't add up... What
about the prize at the Bellaqua
Casino? They're trying to pass that
off as the captain's treasure too,
aren't they?
182:
Isn't that what you were after
originally, Marina?
189:
The Captain had three of those
crystals in total. If I were to guess,
Luca, I'd say the one in your
possession called to you and led
you here.
194:
Perhaps. This Genome Quartz was
given to me by mother... She said
that my father had left it for me to
have.
196:
Though I don't know why he'd do
that... I never met the man.
201:
I see. Well that settles things,
then—from now on, we'll be working
together, Luca!
204:
There's only so much either of us
can do alone here. Plus, you're still
being pursued by... whatever those
things are!
208: I assume everyone's cool with this?
219:
Of course! You had me at "captain's
treasure"! You can't hunt for treasure
without a treasure hunter like me!
223:
Hmm... You've treated me to all this
food... And I hate the idea of being in
someone's debt! I'll help you just to
make us even.
234:
All right! Off to the casino, then. It's
on the main island, so we'll be
needing transportation. Naska?
239:
Leave it to me, Cap'n! I'll get the ship
ready.
243:
Okay, everyone... Let's go get us
some treasure!
